Problem 4

rm(list=ls())
Train <- read.csv("https://www.dropbox.com/s/nnzaeo73zl2ktwg/PA_HW1_train.csv?dl=1", header=TRUE)
Test <- read.csv("https://www.dropbox.com/s/u6iuxfm4lz8isg6/PA_HW1_test.csv?dl=1", header=TRUE)
x1 <- Train$x1
x2 <- Train$x2
x3 <- Train$col
y1 <- Test$x1
y2 <- Test$x2
y3 <- Test$col
library(class)
## Warning: package 'class' was built under R version 3.5.2
KNNA <- knn1(cbind(x1,x2),cbind(x1,x2),cl=x3) # Problem 4a
table(KNNA,Train$col) # There were 0 incorrect observations. This is not good because it means the model is overfitted if 0 / 1750 = 0% of observations are incorrect.
##        
## KNNA    green red
##   green    75   0
##   red       0 100
KNNB <- knn1(cbind(x1,x2),cbind(y1,y2),cl=x3) # Problem 4b
table(KNNB,Test$col) # There were 367 + 352 = 719 incorrect observations. This is not good because 719 / 1750 = 41.0857143% of observations are incorrect.
##        
## KNNB    green red
##   green   398 367
##   red     352 633
